---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
import MonoCaption from '@/components/ui/MonoCaption.astro';
import SericDiagram from '@/components/ui/SericDiagram.astro';
---
<section id="platform" class="border-b border-line">
  <div class="container-page py-24">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <MonoCaption>Platform · Sat Lab Digital Twin</MonoCaption>
      <h2 class="mt-4">
        One digital twin. <em class="italic font-normal text-signal-mint">Any sensor, any satellite, any layer.</em>
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-6">
        The platform separates the real world into five semantic layers. The separation is what lets us scale from a single building to an entire city without crashing — and what lets vegetation detected from orbit live in the same twin as an elevator telemetry stream.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12">
      <SericDiagram />
    </div>

    <p class="mt-10 max-w-2xl">
      Vegetation is the first layer. Buildings, water systems, urban forests — they're layers too, reusing the same twin core. That's the platform thesis.
    </p>

    <a
      href={`${base}/platform`}
      class="mt-8 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-signal-ember no-underline hover:gap-3 transition-all"
    >
      Explore the platform <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
    </a>
  </div>
</section>
